# Coding Standards

This project follows strict coding standards to maintain code quality and consistency.

## Code Style

- **Line Length**: Maximum 88 characters (Black standard)
- **Indentation**: 4 spaces
- **String Quotes**: Double quotes for strings
- **Imports**: Sorted and grouped using isort
  - Standard library imports first
  - Third-party imports second
  - Local application imports last

## Type Hints

- All functions must have type hints
- Use `typing` module for complex types
- No `Any` types allowed (mypy configuration)
- Return types must be explicitly specified

## Documentation

- All modules should have docstrings
- All functions and classes must have docstrings
- Use Google style docstrings
- Include type information in docstrings

## Testing

- Write tests for all new features
- Maintain minimum 80% code coverage
- Use pytest fixtures for test setup
- Name test files as `test_*.py`
- Name test functions as `test_*`

## Code Quality

- No unused imports
- No unused variables
- No duplicate code
- Follow SOLID principles
- Keep functions small and focused

## Git Commit Messages

- Use present tense
- Start with a verb
- Keep first line under 50 characters
- Use body for detailed explanation
- Reference issue numbers if applicable

